I was on Amazon looking for Katt Williams and Sommore popped up as something else to check out. I read the reviews and decided to pick it up. I was not sure what to expect but it was actually pretty funny. I would definitely recommend it for anyone who enjoys good standup comedy. Be warned, she curses and talks about the things that people go through in life from being a child through their adult hood. If you are looking at comedy videos trying to decide what you should get, I would suggest you pick up Sommore for a real good laugh. Set the mood....Tell the kids to go into the other room, pour you some Hennessy, burn you some incense and get ready to laugh! YMMV...NEOSOUL06.

I've been a fan of Sommore since the Queens of Comedy special a few years ago. But this time, Sommore has the entire stage to herself for 90 minutes. As always, she's got a vulgar view of life. But it's always a little bit of truth mixed in with a LOT of funny commentary. If you're a fan of Sommore, then this is absolutely worth the buy. If you're new to the Sommore experience, and just looking for something that will make you laugh (and can handle a LOT of vulgarity), then this DVD is absolutely worth the buy, and I don't think you'll be disappointed.

  Thanks for your time folks.
  Sincerely, R.A. McDowell

I didn't have to preview the DVD because after all, it was Sommore, one of the original Queens of Comedy. I make it a point to check out her show whenever she comes to my area.  She's had funnier rooutines but this DVD has its moments.  The funniest bit is when she's talking about partying with her hood girls and the girls from the office.  That was hillarious.  I hope she puts out another one soon. All in all it's entertaining, IT'S SOMOORE!
